				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the difference between a neck lift and a facelift?</h3>
					<p>A neck lift specifically addresses aging in the neck and jawline area, including sagging skin, muscle bands, and excess fat. A facelift addresses the entire lower face and may also include the neck. Many patients choose to combine both procedures for comprehensive facial rejuvenation.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long does neck lift surgery take?</h3>
					<p>Neck lift surgery typically takes two to four hours, depending on the techniques involved and whether additional procedures are performed simultaneously. The procedure is usually performed on an outpatient basis, allowing patients to return home the same day.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long is the recovery after a neck lift?</h3>
					<p>Most patients can return to work and light activities within two to three weeks. Full recovery, including resolution of all swelling and final results, takes approximately three to six months. Strenuous activities should be avoided for at least four weeks.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Are neck lift results permanent?</h3>
					<p>Neck lift results are long-lasting, typically five to ten years or more. The procedure addresses the structural changes of aging, and while the aging process continues, patients maintain a significantly more youthful appearance than they would without the surgery.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What are the risks of neck lift surgery?</h3>
